WEBVTT

00:07.521 --> 00:09.523
<i>♪ MTV ♪</i>

00:11.992 --> 00:13.561
<i>You suppose
I did something to make</i>

00:13.661 --> 00:15.228
<i>the Almighty angry?</i>

00:15.328 --> 00:18.065
He's just teaching you that
it's hard and takes patience.

00:18.165 --> 00:20.568
Patience ain't gonna
put money in our pocket.

00:20.668 --> 00:24.337
How many mouths you got to feed
with no harvest?

00:24.438 --> 00:26.006
What's your offer?

00:26.106 --> 00:28.442
Sign you up as a posse man.

00:28.542 --> 00:30.343
Welcome to the Dead Line.

00:30.444 --> 00:34.081
<i>Out here, there ain't no laws,
only outlaws.</i>

00:36.550 --> 00:39.386
Watch the legs now.
She a precious thing.

00:40.554 --> 00:41.889
What's your name?

00:41.989 --> 00:43.423
Arthur Mayberry, ma'am.

00:46.226 --> 00:48.228
Come on out with your hands up.

00:53.734 --> 00:54.968
What the hell did you do?

00:56.970 --> 00:59.907
- I hit another white man.
- Not that deputy?

01:01.542 --> 01:04.478
I took some of your earnestness
to Judge Parker.

01:04.578 --> 01:09.382
And he wants to make you
a goddamn Deputy U.S. Marshal.

01:13.153 --> 01:15.055
<i>♪ slow, wistful music ♪</i>

01:39.513 --> 01:40.881
Mm.

01:50.758 --> 01:54.995
Don't you go meeting everybody
without me now.

01:57.865 --> 02:00.968
Make us proud, you hear?

03:06.734 --> 03:08.468
You help me?

03:08.568 --> 03:10.971
I was just hungry.

03:12.272 --> 03:14.507
Mr. Yeager came after me.

03:15.943 --> 03:18.912
I tried to push him
away, but then he...

03:19.012 --> 03:20.914
<i>♪ slow, somber music ♪</i>

03:23.150 --> 03:25.385
There was so much blood.

03:33.927 --> 03:36.029
Bass.

03:49.142 --> 03:51.178
Sit, please.

04:02.823 --> 04:06.626
I suppose today is momentous.

04:07.427 --> 04:10.030
You'll have to forgive me
if I move faster

04:10.130 --> 04:12.332
than the dignity
of the occasion requires,

04:12.432 --> 04:13.801
but I have a full docket,

04:13.901 --> 04:17.570
and I try to save
what dignity I still possess

04:17.671 --> 04:19.139
for the courtroom.

04:21.041 --> 04:23.744
I was encouraged to hire you

04:23.844 --> 04:25.679
for the color of your skin.

04:25.779 --> 04:30.450
Because the Indians would listen
to someone like you.

04:30.550 --> 04:31.852
May be true,

04:31.952 --> 04:33.821
but that's not why
I called you in.

04:33.921 --> 04:38.325
I need a man with a good gun
and a straight spine.

04:38.425 --> 04:40.427
You up for the task?

04:41.428 --> 04:45.032
I wouldn't be sitting here
in my Sunday best if I wasn't.

04:45.866 --> 04:47.968
It's hard work,

04:48.068 --> 04:49.636
it exacts a toll.

04:49.737 --> 04:53.106
Few men survive long enough
to be good at it.

04:53.206 --> 04:57.177
And those that do
end up like Sherrill Lynn.

04:57.277 --> 04:59.713
I ain't ever gonna be
Sherrill Lynn.

04:59.813 --> 05:02.783
Well, let's make it official.
May I?

05:09.022 --> 05:11.191
Oh.

05:11.291 --> 05:14.061
Your Good Book's
got some stories of its own.

05:14.161 --> 05:16.329
- That it does.
- Well, you'll have

05:16.429 --> 05:19.466
to enlighten me
one of these days.

05:30.143 --> 05:31.711
Repeat after me.

05:31.812 --> 05:34.347
I, Bass Reeves,

05:34.447 --> 05:36.316
do solemnly swear...

05:36.416 --> 05:39.452
I, Bass Reeves,
do solemnly swear...

05:39.552 --> 05:41.721
...that I will
faithfully execute...

05:41.822 --> 05:43.723
...that I will faithfully execute...

05:43.824 --> 05:45.225
...all lawful precepts

05:45.325 --> 05:47.660
directed to the Marshal
of the United States...

05:47.761 --> 05:49.262
...all lawful precepts

05:49.362 --> 05:51.765
directed to the Marshal
of the United States...

05:51.865 --> 05:54.935
...for the Western District
of Arkansas...

05:55.035 --> 05:56.303
...for the Western District

05:56.403 --> 05:57.637
of Arkansas...

05:57.737 --> 06:00.240
...without malice
or partiality...

06:00.340 --> 06:02.609
...and without malice
or partiality...

06:02.709 --> 06:05.779
...perform the duties
of Deputy Marshal...

06:05.879 --> 06:08.548
...perform the duties of
Deputy Marshal...

06:08.648 --> 06:11.218
...and take only
my lawful fees...

06:11.318 --> 06:13.086
...take only my lawful fees...

06:13.186 --> 06:14.554
...so help me God.

06:15.355 --> 06:17.424
...so help me God.

06:17.524 --> 06:19.893
<i>♪ slow, plaintive music ♪</i>

06:26.066 --> 06:27.667
You've got miles to ride.

06:27.767 --> 06:30.537
Godspeed the horses.

06:30.637 --> 06:31.872
Thank you.

06:41.548 --> 06:43.583
Judge Parker, if I may.

06:45.252 --> 06:47.554
The boy waiting outside.

06:49.256 --> 06:50.757
He need help.

06:50.858 --> 06:54.527
That boy needs a lawyer.

06:58.631 --> 07:00.667
Yes, sir.

07:01.969 --> 07:03.871
Winston,

07:03.971 --> 07:06.273
bring the boy in.

07:33.200 --> 07:35.102
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

08:42.635 --> 08:45.038
<i>♪ slow, tense music ♪</i>

09:03.356 --> 09:05.993
You needing help?

09:06.093 --> 09:07.494
Don't you know it.

09:07.594 --> 09:09.096
If I had another set of hands...

09:09.196 --> 09:10.663
Sir, we ought to--

09:10.763 --> 09:12.865
Andreas Wagner. I'm helping you.

09:31.951 --> 09:33.953
Thank you very much,
Mr. Fogner.

09:34.054 --> 09:37.024
- Billy Crow, in your debt.
- You're welcome.

09:37.924 --> 09:39.459
Good afternoon, gentlemen.

09:42.462 --> 09:44.631
Hands up.

09:45.532 --> 09:47.434
Mouths shut.

10:15.262 --> 10:17.364
<i>Nein. Bitte.</i>

10:19.099 --> 10:21.434
<i>Nein, nein, nein.</i>

10:22.369 --> 10:24.471
No! No!

10:40.553 --> 10:42.622
This one just came in.

10:45.358 --> 10:48.595
That ought to be a good one
for your first outing.

10:48.695 --> 10:51.030
Any tips for a first-timer?

10:51.131 --> 10:53.800
Oh, hon.

10:53.900 --> 10:57.970
All you need to know
is that I run this circus.

10:58.071 --> 11:00.340
Listen to Florence,
and you'll do just fine.

11:00.440 --> 11:02.609
Ma'am.

11:09.516 --> 11:11.684
You mind?

11:13.186 --> 11:15.122
I might.

11:16.323 --> 11:19.025
Depends who's asking.

11:19.126 --> 11:20.727
Garrett Montgomery.

11:21.661 --> 11:23.263
Never heard of him.

11:23.363 --> 11:24.697
Oh, I'm all right.

11:24.797 --> 11:27.500
You just ask Florence in there.

11:33.273 --> 11:35.074
"Billy Crow.

11:35.175 --> 11:38.511
Wanted in connection
with a stagecoach robbery."

11:38.611 --> 11:40.780
I can help you with that,
Deputy Reeves.

11:42.349 --> 11:44.151
You got a posse man yet?

11:44.251 --> 11:46.253
Suppose you're a posse man?

11:46.353 --> 11:47.654
Rode with Heck Thomas,

11:47.754 --> 11:49.822
Bud Ledbetter.

11:51.391 --> 11:52.759
Put in my fair share of miles

11:52.859 --> 11:54.461
and know this country
like the back of my hand.

11:54.561 --> 11:56.563
Three dollars there,
three dollars back.

11:56.663 --> 11:59.532
Be the best six dollars
you'd ever spend.

12:05.405 --> 12:06.873
Gonna hold you to that.

12:06.973 --> 12:08.675
Yes, sir.

12:08.775 --> 12:11.411
<i>♪ wistful music ♪</i>

12:34.267 --> 12:37.069
I ain't one to talk a donkey's
hind leg off or anything,

12:37.170 --> 12:41.073
but a little conversation goes
a long way, especially out here.

12:50.283 --> 12:51.984
Got any children, Garrett?

12:52.084 --> 12:55.422
Oh, yes, sir. Boy and a girl,
another on the way.

12:55.522 --> 12:57.023
You?

12:57.123 --> 12:58.891
Got four of my own

12:58.991 --> 13:01.528
and number five due any day.

13:03.196 --> 13:06.599
Planning on doing this
for a spell.

13:06.699 --> 13:09.802
All goes well,
you got a job with me.

13:11.137 --> 13:14.574
You'll be saving my hide with
this ongoing employment, Deputy.

13:14.674 --> 13:16.576
Like I say,

13:16.676 --> 13:18.911
all goes well.

13:26.118 --> 13:28.221
<i>♪ slow, gentle music ♪</i>

13:49.609 --> 13:52.144
Fold those nice and even.

13:52.245 --> 13:53.746
All right.

13:56.115 --> 13:57.617
Real soon, I'm gonna need you

13:57.717 --> 13:59.352
to shoulder
a lot more responsibility.

13:59.452 --> 14:01.053
Once the little ones are fed

14:01.153 --> 14:02.989
in the afternoon and napping,

14:03.089 --> 14:05.258
you'll need
to start in on supper.

14:05.358 --> 14:07.360
And after they eat,
you'll need to tidy up.

14:07.460 --> 14:09.095
And I don't want no dirty pots

14:09.195 --> 14:12.365
- and pans in my kitchen.
- All right.

14:15.268 --> 14:17.904
Time for you to start teaching
Harriet now, too.

14:18.004 --> 14:20.773
She'll be a good little helper.

14:24.544 --> 14:25.812
Ooh!

14:27.547 --> 14:28.915
Oh.

14:29.015 --> 14:32.051
- Mama.
- Hmm?

14:34.120 --> 14:37.657
Oh.

14:40.259 --> 14:41.494
Oh.

14:41.594 --> 14:42.995
Stop!

14:43.095 --> 14:45.197
<i>♪ slow, plaintive music ♪</i>

14:56.543 --> 14:58.511
Pay no mind.

14:58.611 --> 15:00.380
Wouldn't be doing our job right

15:00.480 --> 15:03.850
if we didn't rub a few
malefactors the wrong way.

15:05.652 --> 15:07.854
Ask me, hundred to one,

15:07.954 --> 15:11.257
the Underwood Gang's
behind that stagecoach robbery.

15:12.625 --> 15:14.494
You know something I don't?

15:14.594 --> 15:16.329
Female outlaw

15:16.429 --> 15:19.932
the hoopleheads described
in their complaint?

15:20.032 --> 15:22.569
I've come across before.

15:22.669 --> 15:24.771
Woman's pure venom.

15:24.871 --> 15:27.106
Runs with Huff Underwood.

15:27.940 --> 15:29.476
Two hundred to one,

15:29.576 --> 15:33.145
somebody in the hotel know where
they're conducting business.

15:34.947 --> 15:37.717
You know more than you let on.

15:39.886 --> 15:42.254
That ought to scare you.

15:48.260 --> 15:51.163
"H-O...

15:51.263 --> 15:54.200
- T--"
- I know what it say.

15:55.201 --> 15:56.335
This a-way.

16:09.582 --> 16:12.118
Don't you step another foot
toward them tables, Garrett.

16:12.218 --> 16:14.521
Easy, amigo.

16:14.621 --> 16:19.291
I'm just introducing my friend
here to your fine establishment.

16:19.392 --> 16:21.193
Unless your friend wants
to pony up the tin

16:21.293 --> 16:25.231
that you owe this establishment,
then I want you out.

16:26.466 --> 16:28.167
You have a debt here?

16:28.267 --> 16:30.870
Man's got a debt everywhere.

16:32.405 --> 16:35.642
I love them cards
like I love women.

16:36.443 --> 16:40.212
Just the difference is
cards don't love back.

16:41.180 --> 16:45.217
Better off tending horses
than hustling.

16:53.760 --> 16:56.796
Barkeep.

16:57.764 --> 16:59.432
Sherrill Lynn come by yesterday.

16:59.532 --> 17:02.001
Drank up all my whiskey.

17:02.101 --> 17:04.537
Broke three of my chairs.

17:05.337 --> 17:07.607
Tell me you didn't come
for my gin.

17:08.407 --> 17:11.243
How 'bout you quench my thirst
another way?

17:12.111 --> 17:13.946
Looking for a Billy Crow.

17:14.046 --> 17:15.848
Ain't nested here,

17:15.948 --> 17:17.817
far as I know.

17:17.917 --> 17:20.186
How about the Underwood Gang?

17:21.821 --> 17:23.623
Well, goddamn.

17:23.723 --> 17:25.858
If that don't beat the Dutch.

17:25.958 --> 17:28.861
That's two pair.
You can take that one.

17:30.697 --> 17:32.198
Seat taken?

17:32.298 --> 17:34.333
Ain't never seen you
around here.

17:35.334 --> 17:39.572
More than happy
to take a lawman's salary.

17:43.142 --> 17:45.377
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

17:54.120 --> 17:55.955
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

18:10.937 --> 18:14.507
You are crooked
as a hare's hind leg.

18:47.006 --> 18:50.209
Knew you were
holding back on me.

19:07.459 --> 19:09.495
I'll call you.

19:44.130 --> 19:47.433
I ain't falling
for your fooling no more.

19:50.670 --> 19:51.938
I'm all in.

19:58.745 --> 20:00.613
Call.

20:00.713 --> 20:02.581
Two pair.

20:20.199 --> 20:22.769
You Black son of a bitch!

20:22.869 --> 20:24.971
Didn't come to take your money.

20:26.138 --> 20:28.340
How about I return that pot

20:28.440 --> 20:31.077
in exchange for information.

20:31.177 --> 20:33.680
How about
we just kill you instead?

20:34.681 --> 20:36.315
Could try.

20:36.415 --> 20:40.352
But you'd be going after
a Deputy U.S. Marshal,

20:40.452 --> 20:43.222
and there's a half a dozen
more outside.

20:43.322 --> 20:45.758
Hell.

20:45.858 --> 20:48.560
He's bluffing again, Big Al.

20:48.661 --> 20:51.130
Want to wager on that?

21:02.441 --> 21:05.311
In that rig past the corral.

21:10.983 --> 21:14.053
<i>♪ slow, dramatic music ♪</i>

21:17.189 --> 21:19.325
Go around the other side.

21:43.349 --> 21:45.317
You Billy Crow?

21:46.118 --> 21:49.121
Well, uh,
sorry to disappoint you, sir.

21:56.595 --> 22:00.232
I was told I'd find
a Billy Crow around here.

22:03.970 --> 22:06.605
Beautiful coach you got here.

22:06.705 --> 22:09.208
Are you under obligation
to keep banking hours

22:09.308 --> 22:10.910
with a rig like this?

22:11.010 --> 22:14.513
Sure as hell got no obligation
to answer to the likes of you.

22:17.950 --> 22:20.019
Minute your boy sings,

22:20.119 --> 22:22.688
we'll have a writ for you.

22:22.789 --> 22:24.857
Your pal Huff, too.

22:25.657 --> 22:27.894
Why don't you bring
that old Judge Parker

22:27.994 --> 22:29.328
around here next time?

22:29.428 --> 22:32.064
I could introduce him
and that noose of his

22:32.164 --> 22:34.333
to the underside of my carriage.

22:37.069 --> 22:40.306
Come to think of it, uh,
name's familiar.

22:40.406 --> 22:42.875
Is a bit of a looker,
this Billy Crow, ain't he?

22:42.975 --> 22:44.877
I think I saw him packing up
a wagon this morning.

22:44.977 --> 22:48.848
Wouldn't be surprised if he was
halfway to Muskogee by now.

22:51.183 --> 22:53.319
Got to admit,

22:53.419 --> 22:56.422
certain likeness,
wouldn't you agree?

23:14.473 --> 23:17.009
Mind my hat. Shoot.

23:17.109 --> 23:19.078
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

23:19.178 --> 23:20.712
Shoot.

23:35.061 --> 23:37.796
<i>♪ gentle, wistful music ♪</i>

23:56.916 --> 23:57.950
Sally.

24:05.424 --> 24:08.027
Piano I delivered,

24:08.127 --> 24:10.162
that was for your mother?

24:10.262 --> 24:11.697
Mm-hmm.

24:11.797 --> 24:15.267
She fell in love with music
when it was all she had.

24:16.668 --> 24:19.138
Looks like y'all got
a nice big family now.

24:19.238 --> 24:21.407
I'd like it better if

24:21.507 --> 24:23.342
I didn't have to be chasing
Alice and Newland

24:23.442 --> 24:24.610
all over creation.

24:24.710 --> 24:27.813
And now,
with a new one on the way,

24:27.914 --> 24:29.815
I'm really in for it.

24:29.916 --> 24:33.385
What would you rather be doing?
Besides walking with me.

24:33.485 --> 24:35.387
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

24:37.456 --> 24:39.791
Mrs. Green got me
this new book of poems.

24:39.892 --> 24:43.395
Barely had a chance
to crack the spine.

24:45.164 --> 24:48.367
I bet your parents
don't bother you with chores

24:48.467 --> 24:51.570
'cause
you a working man already.

24:52.871 --> 24:54.640
I'm an orphan.

24:58.044 --> 24:59.378
It's all right.

24:59.478 --> 25:01.513
You didn't have any way to know.

25:02.314 --> 25:04.383
I'm sorry.

25:08.087 --> 25:10.289
Mama passed when...

25:10.389 --> 25:13.025
I was five, and...

25:13.125 --> 25:15.394
my daddy died in the war.

25:16.929 --> 25:19.565
You're blessed with a lot
of love in your life.

25:20.933 --> 25:22.701
Keep hold of it.

25:30.809 --> 25:33.045
Just tell Parker what you know.

25:33.145 --> 25:35.047
He a fair man.

25:35.147 --> 25:37.483
Fair man?

25:37.583 --> 25:40.452
He hung 12 men
on his first day in court.

25:40.552 --> 25:41.920
Just ain't no winning.

25:42.021 --> 25:45.157
I name names to Parker,
they'll kill me.

25:45.257 --> 25:47.994
If I keep my trap shut,
I'll rot in Hell on the Border.

25:48.094 --> 25:49.461
That's if they don't kill me

25:49.561 --> 25:51.263
before y'all get me
to Fort Smith.

25:51.363 --> 25:54.066
Oh, I'm getting you
to Fort Smith.

25:54.166 --> 25:56.335
I'm a dead man.

25:56.435 --> 25:57.769
Y'all looking at a ghost.

25:57.869 --> 26:00.872
You don't come at Huff Underwood
with nothing.

26:00.973 --> 26:02.341
You don't rat him out.

26:02.441 --> 26:04.243
And you don't force
his one-time,

26:04.343 --> 26:07.980
reluctant, low-ranking employee
to rat him out, either.

26:20.459 --> 26:21.927
Hey.

26:23.029 --> 26:25.064
How about
I get a quick fire going?

26:25.164 --> 26:27.366
And give up our location?

26:29.235 --> 26:31.603
Hadn't thought of that.

26:33.939 --> 26:36.842
Three dollars here
and three dollars back

26:36.942 --> 26:38.044
to freeze my nuts.

26:38.144 --> 26:40.112
Rather be losing my shirt
at a card table.

26:40.212 --> 26:42.914
Least I'd be able
to feel my hands and feet.

26:43.015 --> 26:44.550
Ain't that cold.

26:44.650 --> 26:47.853
Hell, once,
I had this pot-bellied stove,

26:47.953 --> 26:50.822
forged in Massachusetts
for them northern winters.

26:50.922 --> 26:53.392
Sat right in the heart
of my beautiful home,

26:53.492 --> 26:55.294
just outside Fort Smith.

26:56.362 --> 26:59.931
You get that thing going during
the middle of a cold snap,

27:00.032 --> 27:02.934
practically warmed
the neighbor's house, too.

27:03.035 --> 27:04.936
What happened to it?

27:06.672 --> 27:08.240
Had to sell it.

27:08.340 --> 27:11.677
Along with lots of other things.

27:11.777 --> 27:14.380
You got enough luck
to survive all this, kid,

27:14.480 --> 27:16.782
you stay away from the cards.

27:23.455 --> 27:26.792
I know where they hid the money
they took from that stagecoach.

27:29.261 --> 27:32.664
I hear you clucking, but there
ain't no nest, Billy Crow.

27:32.764 --> 27:35.033
No, there-there's jewelry
there, too.

27:35.134 --> 27:37.035
Huff didn't want
to pawn it off too quick.

27:37.136 --> 27:38.570
Avoid suspicion and all.

27:38.670 --> 27:41.840
I'm telling
the God's honest truth here.

27:42.808 --> 27:45.444
Not really in a position to lie.

27:45.544 --> 27:48.947
You been sitting on that
all night?

27:50.249 --> 27:52.318
We might investigate this, Bass.

27:52.418 --> 27:53.852
No.

27:53.952 --> 27:56.655
Could split the money
and whatever else there is.

27:56.755 --> 27:57.856
Nobody would ever know.

27:57.956 --> 27:59.991
We say Billy Crow flew away.

28:00.092 --> 28:02.261
Oh, oh, oh,
you'll never hear from me again.

28:02.361 --> 28:03.995
I'll bound a rail to California.

28:05.397 --> 28:06.932
You both talk too much.

28:07.032 --> 28:09.000
You don't understand, Bass.

28:09.101 --> 28:10.469
I got a wife and kids

28:10.569 --> 28:12.704
sleeping in a bed
more suitable for pigs.

28:12.804 --> 28:16.375
Our job is to take this boy
alive to Fort Smith.

28:17.309 --> 28:21.113
That's what we're gonna do.
Took an oath.

28:21.213 --> 28:22.981
I didn't.

28:28.487 --> 28:31.523
I ain't asking.

28:31.623 --> 28:33.592
I'm telling.

28:40.466 --> 28:43.569
<i>♪ tense, dramatic music ♪</i>

28:45.337 --> 28:47.273
Whoa.

28:47.373 --> 28:48.940
Whoa, fellas.

28:53.078 --> 28:55.481
You think
another white posse man's

28:55.581 --> 28:56.682
gonna ride out with you?

28:56.782 --> 28:59.785
Help you like I have?

28:59.885 --> 29:02.120
And now you gonna shoot me?

29:02.221 --> 29:04.623
No.

29:04.723 --> 29:06.658
But they will.

29:21.773 --> 29:23.509
Hope your feet
as fast as your mouth.

29:53.605 --> 29:55.674
Billy Crow.

29:55.774 --> 29:57.376
Where you at?

29:57.476 --> 29:59.245
We ain't gonna hurt you.

30:00.412 --> 30:03.649
Give us sign of that lawman
so we can end this.

30:04.483 --> 30:06.252
Mother of God.

30:06.352 --> 30:09.921
- I told you I was gonna die.
- Not today.

30:19.665 --> 30:21.500
Stay here.

30:21.600 --> 30:23.769
<i>♪ energetic, dramatic music ♪</i>

30:53.499 --> 30:56.468
<i>♪ slow, tense music ♪</i>

31:27.999 --> 31:29.901
Keep your current path,

31:30.001 --> 31:32.704
this your fate, Billy Crow.

31:33.605 --> 31:35.507
Empty boots

31:35.607 --> 31:38.276
strung up on a lawman's saddle.

31:43.382 --> 31:45.351
Thank you, Deputy.

32:07.406 --> 32:10.442
Oh, oh. Oh...

32:11.443 --> 32:13.278
Oh...

32:15.581 --> 32:17.082
Sally!

32:20.552 --> 32:21.987
I'll go fetch Miss Bennett.

32:22.087 --> 32:23.989
This one coming faster
than lightning in a storm.

32:24.089 --> 32:26.224
Help me to the kitchen.

32:34.232 --> 32:37.102
Go fetch some water for
the stove and get the linen.

32:37.202 --> 32:40.772
- We'll make do.
- Yes, Mama.

32:45.110 --> 32:47.212
<i>♪ slow, gentle music ♪</i>

32:51.182 --> 32:54.219
How the hell did you learn
to shoot like that?

32:55.554 --> 32:57.155
You mean for a Black man?

32:57.255 --> 32:59.124
No, I mean,

32:59.224 --> 33:01.793
how the hell did you learn
to shoot like that?

33:02.928 --> 33:05.764
How about you do us both a favor

33:05.864 --> 33:09.200
and never speak on this
ever again.

33:34.092 --> 33:36.327
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

34:02.954 --> 34:05.491
Billy Crow. Prisoner.

34:05.591 --> 34:08.159
Your prisoner. Your manacles.

34:14.165 --> 34:18.837
Now, keep your head down
and your mouth shut.

34:18.937 --> 34:20.806
Hey,

34:20.906 --> 34:24.175
I make it out of here,
how do I get to do what you do?

34:27.312 --> 34:30.381
Was you telling the truth
about the money?

34:30.482 --> 34:31.783
Eagle Pass.

34:31.883 --> 34:34.920
There's a pair of sister oaks,
roots entwined.

34:35.020 --> 34:37.455
It's buried at the base.

34:56.007 --> 34:57.709
<i>Isham Saunders,</i>

34:57.809 --> 35:01.079
<i>after a fair trial
and an able defense,</i>

35:01.179 --> 35:03.649
this jury of your countrymen

35:03.749 --> 35:05.517
has found you guilty

35:05.617 --> 35:09.087
of a most foul
and aggravated murder.

35:09.187 --> 35:12.457
You are hereby sentenced
to be hanged by the neck

35:12.558 --> 35:14.492
until you are dead.

35:16.161 --> 35:18.930
<i>♪ slow, somber music ♪</i>

35:19.030 --> 35:20.966
Myson Davis.

35:22.333 --> 35:25.871
I have heard your tale
of misfortune.

35:25.971 --> 35:29.541
I understand what hunger
and deprivation

35:29.641 --> 35:31.509
can drive a person to do,

35:31.610 --> 35:33.344
but it's no different

35:33.444 --> 35:35.480
from the plight
of all the other men

35:35.581 --> 35:39.885
who stand before me
on any given day.

35:39.985 --> 35:42.520
In this chamber,

35:42.621 --> 35:44.222
I must serve

35:44.322 --> 35:47.859
as an instrument of the law.

35:47.959 --> 35:50.796
You have taken a human life.

35:50.896 --> 35:52.798
You have sent a human soul

35:52.898 --> 35:56.001
unprepared to its maker

35:56.101 --> 35:58.369
and made agony for his family,

35:58.469 --> 36:01.139
whom you have rendered husbandless

36:01.239 --> 36:03.575
and fatherless.

36:04.542 --> 36:07.178
For the crime of murder,

36:07.278 --> 36:10.515
this court finds you guilty.

36:12.117 --> 36:13.785
You are hereby sentenced

36:13.885 --> 36:15.553
to be hanged by the neck

36:15.654 --> 36:18.023
until you are dead.

36:33.338 --> 36:36.708
Okay, Deputy, go on in.

36:48.687 --> 36:50.656
Sit down, please.

36:54.559 --> 36:57.162
You had a bit
of a time out there?

36:58.664 --> 37:01.199
Well, sir, um...

37:01.299 --> 37:03.234
Posse man Montgomery

37:03.334 --> 37:06.137
died heroically
in the line of duty.

37:07.973 --> 37:11.109
They ambushed us
to free my prisoner.

37:14.846 --> 37:17.082
About that Billy Crow...

37:18.349 --> 37:21.853
He not a bad soul,
just confused.

37:22.654 --> 37:26.725
Confusion isn't much
of a defense.

37:26.825 --> 37:28.526
No, sir,

37:28.626 --> 37:30.161
but he told me

37:30.261 --> 37:33.064
where the German man's
money buried.

37:33.164 --> 37:35.400
Noted.

37:47.145 --> 37:49.047
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

38:32.157 --> 38:34.125
You all right?

38:36.762 --> 38:38.296
Are you?

38:40.766 --> 38:42.533
I am now.

39:47.365 --> 39:48.533
Ole Mister Sundown.

39:48.633 --> 39:51.837
<i>Now he was a slave catcher.</i>

39:51.937 --> 39:53.504
<i>Some say</i>

39:53.604 --> 39:57.108
he roam the dark even now.

39:57.208 --> 39:59.077
Finding fresh slaves.

39:59.177 --> 40:02.580
<i>When you see ole Mister Sundown,</i>

40:02.680 --> 40:04.482
<i>you never see the sun
come up again.</i>

40:04.582 --> 40:06.351
<i>You ain't no law here.</i>

40:06.451 --> 40:08.286
<i>This here's Hell.</i>

40:08.386 --> 40:10.355
Until God say otherwise,

40:10.455 --> 40:13.158
<i>I'm the only law there is.</i>
